Neither Olivia nor Robert can give an afternoon report. If Nina gives a report, then on the next day Helen and Irving must both give reports, unless Nina's report is given on Wednesday.

If George, Nina, and Robert give reports and they do so on different days from one another, which one of the following could be true?
Choices:
A) Helen gives a report on Wednesday.
B) Nina gives a report on Monday.
C) Nina gives a report on Tuesday.
D) Olivia gives a report on Monday.
E) Robert gives a report on Wednesday.
chain_of_thought: George can only present on Tuesday. Nina can present on any day, but if she presents on Monday, then Helen and Irving must present on Tuesday. This is not possible since George is presenting on Tuesday. Therefore, Nina must present on Tuesday or Wednesday. If Nina presents on Tuesday, then Helen and Irving must present on Wednesday. If Nina presents on Wednesday, then Helen and Irving must present on Tuesday. In either case, Robert must present on Monday. This is option D.
full_output:
<cot_start>
George can only present on Tuesday. Nina can present on any day, but if she presents on Monday, then Helen and Irving must present on Tuesday. This is not possible since George is presenting on Tuesday. Therefore, Nina must present on Tuesday or Wednesday. If Nina presents on Tuesday, then Helen and Irving must present on Wednesday. If Nina presents on Wednesday, then Helen and Irving must present on Tuesday. In either case, Robert must present on Monday. This is option D.
<cot_end>
Answer: D

Rottweilers are not featured on day 7, nor on any day that features Himalayans. Therefore, Rottweilers must be featured on days 3, 5, and 7.
Siamese must be featured on day 7, as it is the only breed left.
Therefore, the order is Siamese, Himalayan, Manx, Himalayan, Rottweiler, Himalayan, Siamese.
This is option D.

full_output:

<cot_end>

A chemistry class has six lab sessions scheduled over three days—Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday—one session heing held each morning and one each afternoon. Each session will be led by a different lab assistant—Julio, Kevin, Lan, Nessa, Olivia, or Rebecca. The assignment of lab assistants to sessions is constrained as follows: Kevin and Rebecca must lead sessions that meet on the same day. Lan and Olivia cannot lead sessions that meet on the same day. Nessa must lead an afternoon session. Julio's session must meet on an earlier day of the week than Olivia's.

Which one of the following could he an accurate assignment of lab assistants to morning and afternoon sessions, respectively, on the three days?
Choices:
A) Wednesday: Rebecca, Kevin Thursday: Julio, Lan Friday: Nessa, Olivia
B) Wednesday: Olivia, Nessa Thursday: Julio, Lan Friday: Kevin, Rebecca
C) Wednesday: Lan, Kevin Thursday: Rebecca, Julio Friday: Olivia, Nessa
D) Wednesday: Kevin, Rebecca Thursday: Julio, Nessa Friday: Olivia, Lan
E) Wednesday: Julio, Lan Thursday: Olivia, Nessa Friday: Rebecca, Kevin

Lan and Olivia cannot lead sessions that meet on the same day. This means they can only be in options B, C, or E.
Nessa must lead an afternoon session. This means she can only be in options A, C, or D.
Julio's session must meet on an earlier day of the week than Olivia's. This means Julio can only be in options A, B, or C.
Considering all the constraints, option C is the only one that satisfies all the conditions.

There are more of the sales representatives working in Zone 3 than in Zone 2.

If more sales representatives work in Zone 1 than in Zone 3, then which one of the following could be true?
Choices:
A) Kim works in Zone 2.
B) Mahr works in Zone 2.
C) Parra works in Zone 3.
D) Tiao works in Zone 1.
E) Udall works in Zone 3.

If more sales representatives work in Zone 1 than in Zone 3, then Zone 1 must have at least 2 representatives, and Zone 3 must have at most 1 representative.
Since Parra and Quinn work in the same zone, and Stuckey and Udall work in the same zone, the only way to satisfy the condition that there are more representatives in Zone 1 than in Zone 3 is if Parra and Tiao are in Zone 1, and Udall and Stuckey are in Zone 3.
This means that Parra works in Zone 1, and Udall works in Zone 3.

Which one of the following could be a complete and accurate list of the sales representatives working in Zone 3?
Choices:
A) Kim, Mahr
B) Kim, Tiao

Therefore, the only option that could be a complete and accurate list of the sales representatives working in Zone 3 is option E.

question:
A maintenance company that takes service requests from three clients—Image, Solide, and Truvest—plans to set targets for its average service response times. Service targets will be set at 3 days, 2 days, or 1 day. Two service targets are set for each client—one for requests received through the maintenance company's website and one for requests received by voicemail. The six targets are set according to the following conditions: None of the clients can have a website target that is longer than its voicemail target. Image's voicemail target must be shorter than the other clients' voicemail targets. Solide's website target must be shorter than Truvest's website target.

If Solide's voicemail target is shorter than Truvest's website target, which one of the following targets could be 2 days?
Choices:
A) Image's website target
B) Image's voicemail target
C) Solide's website target
D) Truvest's voicemail target
E) Truvest's website target
chain_of_thought:
If Solide's voicemail target is shorter than Truvest's website target, then Truvest's website target must be 3 days. This is because Truvest's website target must be longer than Solide's website target.
If Truvest's website target is 3 days, then Solide's website target must be 2 days. This is because Solide's website target must be shorter than Truvest's website target.
If Solide's website target is 2 days, then Solide's voicemail target must be 1 day. This is because Solide's voicemail target must be shorter than its website target.
If Solide's voicemail target is 1 day, then Image's voicemail target must be 2 days. This is because Image's voicemail target must be shorter than Solide's voicemail target.
Therefore, Image's voicemail target could be 2 days.
full_output:
<cot_start>
If Solide's voicemail target is shorter than Truvest's website target, then Truvest's website target must be 3 days. This is because Truvest's website target must be longer than Solide's website target.
If Truvest's website target is 3 days, then Solide's website target must be 2 days. This is because Solide's website target must be shorter than Truvest's website target.
If Solide's website target is 2 days, then Solide's voicemail target must be 1 day. This is because Solide's voicemail target must be shorter than its website target.
If Solide's voicemail target is 1 day, then Image's voicemail target must be 2 days. This is because Image's voicemail target must be shorter than Solide's voicemail target.
Therefore, Image's voicemail target could be 2 days.
<cot_end>

The order in which the articles are edited is fully determined if which one of the following is true?

chain_of_thought:

Since S is first and Q is third, Y must be fifth. This is because S must be earlier than Y.

Since the order of J, G, and R is JGR, and Y is fifth, the order of the articles is S, Q, H, Y, J, G, R.
Since the order of the articles is S, Q, H, Y, J, G, R, H is sixth.

question:
In the Lifestyle, Metro, and Sports sections of tomorrow's newspaper, a total of six different photographs are to appear, exactly two photographs per section. Each of the available photographs was taken by one of three photographers: Fuentes, Gagnon, and Hue. Selection of the photographs is constrained by the following conditions: For each photographer, at least one but no more than three of that photographers photographs must appear. At least one photograph in the Lifestyle section must be by a photographer who has at least one photograph in the Metro section. The number of Hue's photographs in the Lifestyle section must be the same as the number of Fuentes photographs in the Sports section. None of Gagnon's photographs can be in the Sports section.

If one photograph in the Lifestyle section is by Gagnon and one is by Hue, then which one of the following must be true?
Choices:
A) Exactly one photograph in the Metro section is by Fuentes.
B) Exactly one photograph in the Metro section is by Gagnon.
C) Both photographs in the Metro section are by Gagnon.
D) Exactly one photograph in the Sports section is by Hue.
E) Both photographs in the Sports section are by Hue.

D) Exactly one photograph in the Sports section is by Hue.
